h3.p-y-2.display-4 Philosophy

p.
 Innovation is part of our DNA at Mozilla. For us, innovation is not just about
 breakout products that support the open web, it’s about how we make those
 products – with transparency, communication, and a participatory approach.

p.
 This innovation toolkit is designed to empower each and every person at
 Mozilla with a set of tried and true methods to move us forward in building the
 products that support our mission. The toolkit currently focuses on the earlier
 part of product development around insight gathering, ideation, and rapid
 prototyping. This upfront work should flow into a more established product
 development process.

p.
  Each activity includes pertinent information around purpose, outcome, time,
  number of people needed, difficulty, equipment/materials/space, and detailed
  steps. We have also linked out to articles and blog posts that describe methods
  in a way we consider to be a best practice. Our goal is to create a collection
  that leverages our internal knowledge and takes advantage of the great work
  others have contributed in the field.

p.
  The Open Innovation Team has a “train the trainer” mindset where our goal is
  to enable and empower other Mozillians to deploy these methods. However we know
  that is it is sometimes more expedient or preferable to have experienced
  facilitators run a particular session -- in this case the Innovation Team will
  happily support the team directly.  Ask for a facilitator, email us at:
