p.
  The Mozilla manifesto pledges the organization to build and deliver great consumer products that support that manifesto's principles. To do that, we will work by the following product principles:

h3.p-y-2.display-4 Product Principles

ul.list-group
  li.list-group-item We will build products that solve challenges real users face.
  li.list-group-item We will obsessively seek to understand these user challenges by bringing empathy, cultural awareness, and fairness to every challenge.
  li.list-group-item We will not fall in love with the solutions we create, but instead keep our focus on the problems we are trying to solve. We know that there are myriad solutions to a problem, but a solution can only be right or wrong.
  li.list-group-item We will use our muscles to build only after we have uncovered insights, generated multiple ideas, and rapidly prototyped and tested possible solutions.
  li.list-group-item We will take pride in our work but remember that we are building for users, not just ourselves.
  li.list-group-item We will create unique and defensible products with value propositions that are driven by the market.
